section.p:
The spans indicate that two range scans are being performed, and the ranges are overlapping
        with the values 50-100 being scanned twice. To eliminate duplicates N1QL does distinct
        operations on meta().id. When possible, rewriting the query may help eliminate duplicates.
        EXPLAIN SELECT meta().id FROM `travel-sample` WHERE id <= 150;      "spans": [
          {
              "Range": {
                  "High": [
                       "150"
                   ],
                   "Inclusion": 2,
                   "Low": [
                       "null"
                   ]
              }
          }
      ]
